HEADWORD: Woodroof
<hw>Wood"roof`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>wudurofe</ets>. See
<er>Wood</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, and cf. <er>Ruff</er> a plaited
collar.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A little European herb
(<spn>Asperula odorata</spn>) having a pleasant taste. It is sometimes
used for flavoring wine. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Whorl</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

